130:**Transcription errors on clinically significant terms.** Drug names, dosages, and numerical findings are the highest-leverage errors. A dose mis-transcribed as "ten milligrams" instead of "one hundred milligrams" is a ten-fold error hidden in a short phrase. Mitigation: medical-specific ASR with domain vocabulary biasing, explicit post-processing to detect numeric anomalies ("ten milligrams of warfarin" is a red flag for a common mis-recognition), and an emphasis in the clinician review UX on drug names and doses.
